  "instructions": [
    "Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Roll out the pastry dough to a thickness of 1/8 inch.",
    "Place the dough in a 9-inch kadhai or heavy skillet.",
    "In a separate bowl, mix together the yogurt, chopped onion, parsley, egg, mustard seeds, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Add the smoked haddock fillets to the bowl and mix gently to combine.",
    "Spoon the haddock mixture into the pastry-lined kadhai.",
    "Brush the edges of the pastry with unsalted butter.",
    "Fold the pastry over the filling to form a burry shape.",
    "Cut a few slits in the top of the pastry to allow steam to escape.",
    "Place the kadhai in the oven and bake for 25 minutes.",
    "Remove the kadhai from the oven and let it cool for 5 minutes.",
    "Serve the burry warm, garnished with additional parsley if desired."
  ],
